FOOT & MOUTH DISEASE, BOVINE - ISRAEL (04): OIE
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail, a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 24 Jan 2007
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Disease Information, WAHID [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=weekly_report_index&admin=0>

Foot and mouth disease, Israel: Information received on 24 Jan 2007
from Dr. Moshe Chaimovitz, Director, Veterinary Services and Animal
Health, Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development, Beit Dagan, Israel
Summary:
Start date 18 Jan 2007
Date of confirmation of event 24 Jan 2007
Report date 24 Jan 2007
Date submitted to OIE 24 Jan 2007
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of listed disease
Date of previous occurrence December 2005
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent FMD virus O1
Serotype O
Nature of diagnosis: Suspicion, Clinical, Laboratory (basic),
Laboratory (advanced), Necropsy
Report pertains to: Entire country
New Outbreaks
Outbreak 1 (Bet Hashitta) Bet Hashitta, Yizreel, Hazafon
Date of start of outbreak 18 Jan 2007
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not submitted)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Affected animals
Species Cattle
Susceptible 2600
Cases 120
Deaths 1
Destroyed 0
Slaughtered 0
Affected population: The affected population are beef cattle aged
9-11 months. The calves showed classical symptoms of the disease such
as erosions in the mouth and limping. The calves have been vaccinated
between February and April 2006.
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak statistics
Species Cattle
Apparent morbidity rate 4.62 percent
Apparent mortality rate 0.04 percent
Apparent case fatality rate 0.83 percent
Proportion susceptible removed* 0.04 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population either through death,
destruction or slaughter
Epidemiology
Source of infection: Unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: Antigen detection ELISA and pathogen
isolation on cell culture were performed on cattle samples and were
found positive for the virus in the Kimron Veterinary Institute.
Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: National FMD Laboratory, Kimron Veterinary
Institute (National laboratory)
Tests and results
Species Goats
Test antigen (Ag) detection ELISA
Test date 1 Jan 2007
Result Positive
Species Goats
Test pathogen isolation on cell culture
Test date 1 Jan 2007
Result Positive
